Compound statements like this are hard to read. It is difficult to tell at a glance what this is doing, especially since `file` is being reassigned. Something like:

     if file is None:
          files = None
     else:
          files = {"file": file}

would be a lot more readable. A comment explaining why/when this is necessary would also be great.

auto it = std::find_if(fractional_ids.begin(), fractional_ids.end(), [](auto& fractional_id) {return fractional_id.first == resource_id;});
RAY_CHECK(it !=  fractional_ids.end());

double sum = it->second + resource_quantity;
RAY_CHECK(sum <= 1);
 if (sum < 1) {
   it->second = sum;
} else {
   // Return this ID to the whole IDs.
  fractional_ids.erase(it);
